@ijuma Excess in debug logging has been caused by Reflections. We don't control the level that the messages of this external package are printed on, but as I suggested in slack we should consider setting the logger for `org.reflections.*` to `ERROR` (even `WARN` is chatty). 

Regardless, class scanning itself takes some time. 

Therefore I would suggest a combined increase of timeouts and change of logger for reflections.

@msjax No configuration option is required for zookeeper. As zookeeper has already used it correctly for secured cluster
zkUtils = ZkUtils.apply(options.valueOf(zookeeperOption),
                30000,
                30000,
                JaasUtils.isZkSecurityEnabled());
